{
  "texts": [
    "Precision Saccade A fast eye movement that directs the fovea toward a new part of the environment.",
    "Sampling frequency (Hz) How many times per second data are recorded.",
    "Validation A procedure where participants look at fixation targets to evaluate the quality of a calibration.",
    "The descriptions of the terminology apply to human participants with normal anatomy and functioning of the visual system.",
    "For more information about the terms, we refer the reader to the references under 'Further reading'"
  ]
}